5. PF City Builder

Target stakeholders: General public, students, members, policy learners
Game format: City-building strategy game

The player builds a town where workers, employers, hospitals, families, retirees, and government offices interact. Social security coverage affects the prosperity of the city.

If workers are covered under EPFO, the city becomes more stable: retirees receive pension, families receive death benefits, employees save for future, and financial distress reduces.

Learning outcomes:

Players understand EPFO as a social security institution, not just a deduction from salary.

Game mechanics:

More formal employment → more EPF coverage
Good compliance → higher worker trust
Low awareness → more claim rejection
High portability → better workforce mobility
Better grievance system → higher public satisfaction

Gamification:

Social security index, retirement dignity score, worker confidence score, compliance ecosystem rating.
